From 0b364463201982816453b78a593876897500d084 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Juniper Bevensee <juniperbevensee@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 22 May 2026 23:05:44 +1200
Subject: [PATCH 13/27] feat(signal): UUID allowlisting, group invite policy,
 and profile name setting

Port three Signal adapter improvements from old fork as clean patches:

- UUID-based allowlisting: resolves phone numbers to Signal UUIDs at
  startup via listContacts/getUserStatus, with lazy fallback resolution
  on first message. Adds dm_allow_from_uuids and group_allow_from_uuids
  sets for stable identity matching.

- Group invite policy: SIGNAL_GROUP_INVITE_POLICY env var controls
  auto-accept of group invitations. "approved-only" (default) only
  accepts from users in the DM allowlist; "allow-all" accepts from
  anyone. Falls back from joinGroup to updateGroup RPC.

- Profile name setting: SIGNAL_PROFILE_NAME env var sets the bot's
  Signal profile name via updateProfile RPC during connect(). Silent
  no-op when unset; failures logged but never block startup.

Includes 21 tests covering all three features.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
